body:
## Issue

Tests are not running in Clean-room environment.

## Steps to Reproduce

Run 2 tests after another which modify storage state.

## Expected Behavior

Each of them to happen on freshly deployed smart contract (not to have the state changes from previous test).

## Actual Results

Second test fails because first test's state change is persistent 

## Environment

* Operating System: Windows 10
* Ethereum client: Ganache
* Truffle version (`truffle version`): v5.4.18
* node version (`node --version`): v16.13.0
* npm version (`npm --version`): 8.1.0

My tests:

```
const { BN, expectEvent, expectRevert } = require('@openzeppelin/test-helpers');

var chai = require("chai");
const chaiBN = require("chai-bn")(BN);
chai.use(chaiBN);
const expect = chai.expect;

const Library = artifacts.require('./Library.sol');

contract("Library", async (accounts) => {

  const [owner, user] = accounts;

  it("owner shouldn't be able to create the same book twice", async () => {
    let instance = await Library.deployed();
    let bookTitle = "Book 2";
    let bookCopiesCount = 2;

    await instance.createBook(bookTitle, bookCopiesCount);

    await expectRevert(instance.createBook(bookTitle, bookCopiesCount), "Book already exists.");
  });

  it("owner should be able to create a book", async () => {
    let instance = await Library.deployed();
    let bookTitle = "Book 1";
    let bookCopiesCount = 2;
    let bookCopiesCountBN = new BN(bookCopiesCount);

    const result = await instance.createBook(bookTitle, bookCopiesCount);
    
    expect(result.logs[0].args.title).to.equal(bookTitle); 
    expect(await instance.bookStorage(0)).to.have.bignumber.property('availableCount').equal(bookCopiesCountBN);
    expect(await instance.getAllBooks()).to.have.lengthOf(1);
  });

  it("user should't be able to create a book", async () => {
    let instance = await Library.deployed();
    let bookTitle = "Book 2";
    let bookCopiesCount = 2;

    await expectRevert(instance.createBook(bookTitle, bookCopiesCount, {from: user}), "Ownable: caller is not the owner");
  });


});
```
When I run the 3 tests I get the following result:
```
  Contract: Library
    √ owner shouldn't be able to create the same book twice (1593ms)
    1) owner should be able to create a book

    Events emitted during test:
    ---------------------------

    Library.NewBookCreated(
      title: 'Book 1' (type: string),
      id: 1 (type: uint256)
    )


    ---------------------------
    √ user should't be able to create a book (358ms)


  2 passing (3s)
  1 failing

  1) Contract: Library
       owner should be able to create a book:

      AssertionError: expected [ Array(2) ] to have a length of 1 but got 2
      + expected - actual

      -2
      +1

      at Context.<anonymous> (test\Library.test.js:34:50)
      at processTicksAndRejections (node:internal/process/task_queues:96:5)
```

My truffle-config.js:
```
module.exports = {

  networks: {
      develop: {
        port: 7545,
        network_id: "5777",
        host: "127.0.0.1"
    }
  },
  mocha: {
  },
  compilers: {
    solc: {
      version: "0.8.9",
    }
  },
};
```
